utilizing_databases

  Databases allow us to collect, store, retrieve, sort graph, and manipulate data.

  A database is an organized collection of various forms of data.

  Databases are used by many applications web, mobile,services, and more.

  You access the data stored in a database by querying it. 

  EX:
    Relationals:

      RDS
        Good for databases that has relations between the tables.Like when you need to join data ta get the full picture. 

        Support the following DB engines:

          Aurora
          PostgreSQL
          MySQL
          MariaDB
          Oracle
          SQL Server

        Offers high availability and fault tolerance using Multi-AZ deployment option

        AWS manages:
          Automatic software patching
          Automated backups
          Operating system maintenance
          and more

        Launch read replicas across Regions in order to provide enhanced performance and durability.
          
      Aurora

        compatible w/: 
          MySQL 
          Postgres
      
        5x fasater than normal MySQL and 3x faster than normal PostgresSQL      

        Scales automaticlly while providing durability and high availability

        Managed by RDS.


    NoSQL:
      NoSQL it simples means the database it is self describing and it doens't enforce relations like a Relational DB. 
      
      Dynamo:

         NoSQL, key-value database. 

         Fully managed and serverless.

         Non-relational.

         Scales automatically to massive workloads w/ fast performance.

    Graph:
      Neptune:
        Fully managed and grath DB. It supports highly connected datasets.
        Supports highly connected datasets like social media networks.
        Fully managed and serverless
        Fast and reliable

    In-memory:
      ElastiCache:

        Fully managed and serverless

        Compatible w/: 
          Redis 
          Memcached engines

        The data can be lost because it is stored in memory.

        It offers high performance and low latency.

    Document:
      DocumentDB: 
        Supports MongoDB
        Fully managed and serverless

